### 5.4 Appointment Cancellation Trend
**Chart type:** Dual-line time series (actual vs. baseline)
**Module palette:** Appointments (blue)
**Library:** Chart.js

**Context:** Admins track weekly cancellation rates against a rolling baseline to detect scheduling friction, seasonal patterns, or capacity bottlenecks. The dual-line format shows deviation from expected behavior.

**Design decision:** A solid line (actual) paired with a dashed line (baseline) was used rather than two solid lines — making the comparison immediately scannable without a legend lookup. The Appointments palette (blue) distinguishes this from clinical and financial dashboards.

**Business impact:** Earlier identification of scheduling issues, reducing the impact of last-minute cancellations on resource utilization.

